                        Rivetweb README
                        ---------------

 Rivetweb is a minimum requirements Tcl based engine for creating template 
based websites. The only mandatory software you need is the Apache HTTP 
Webserver and Apache Rivet plus some additional packages when specific
features are needed.
 
 Rivetweb relies on Apache Rivet (http://tcl.apache.org/rivet/) for doing 
most of the work needed to create and manipulate content to be displayed in
HTML pages. Rivetweb exploits the ability of Rivet of handling 
templates to structure HTML code into pages having a consistent
appearance thorough a whole website.

 Rivetweb internal machinery and organizazion was entirely developed in 
Tcl/Itcl. Itcl based classes will probably migrate to the TclOO object system. 
Rivetweb was written with an emphasis on indipendence from actual
implementation of its components. Rivetweb aims to evolve to a fully
customizable, extensible framework for simple websites. 

 Current code provides example components (dubbed datasource) that work with 
XML documents bearing both metadata and content of a page. This data source 
implemented in tcl/datasource/xmlchunk.tcl (which does the actual work of reading 
the files, creating and composing menu object and filling Rivetweb database)
can be taken as a model for implementing more data sources.

 From the beginning a basic feature of Rivetweb has been the
ability of faking a dinamically generated website as a consistent 
set of pure HTML pages. This is done by rewriting internal
links as if each of them are pointing to good old static HTML files. 
As a consequence, by means of any mirror tool (e.g. wget), you can recreate 
a local copy of the website completely rewritten in .html files. 
This copy can be thus deployed with *any* webserver or even distributed 
on a Pendrive or a CD-ROM for offline browsing.

 A Rivetweb web site can be running several XHTML/CSS templates at the same 
time, you just switch from one to another by passing the 'template' parameter 
in the URL. This might be useful if you want to test different styles, 
compare them and let your customers decide which is best to their taste.

 Rivetweb is thought to be multilingual. Its page model interface handles
language codes and also menu links and headers can switch from a language
to another language provided your datasource has method for fetching 
content in different languages

Rivetweb has a basic support for extensibility of the markup: 
page creation can be customized adding 'hook' procedures to the code, 
thus adding new data transformations and/or tag expansion.

Rivetweb is entirely free and released under the Apache 2.0 licence.

